from bs4 import BeautifulSoup as bs
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
from tqdm.notebook import tqdm
import requests
import pandas as pd
import os
#########################################
`

def get_code_df():
    '''
         .
    '''
    stock_code = pd.read_html('http://kind.krx.co.kr/corpgeneral/corpList.do?method=download', header=0)[0] 

    #   "" ""   column 
    stock_code = stock_code[['', '']] 

    #  6  6    
    stock_code. = stock_code..map('{:06d}'.format) 
    return stock_code


def get_code(stock_code, corp_name):
    '''
       .
    '''
    code = stock_code.loc[stock_code. == corp_name, ''].item()
    return code


def get_soup(url):
    '''
    beautifulsoup  URL HTML .
    '''
    header = {'user-agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'} #  user-agent   ..   .
    res = requests.get(url, headers=header)
    soup = bs(res.text, 'html.parser')
    return soup


def get_df(rows):
    '''
       .
    '''
    df = pd.DataFrame()
    for idx, row in enumerate(rows):
        time = row.find('td', align='center')
        if time:
            df.loc[idx, ''] = time.text

        price = row.find('td', class_='num')
        if price:
            df.loc[idx, ''] = price.text

    df = df[df[''] != '\xa0'] #  .
    df = df.dropna().reset_index(drop=True) # NA 
    return df


def crawl_price_data():
    '''
        .
    '''
    stock_code = get_code_df()
    #  TOP 5 
    corp_list = ['', 'SK', 'NAVER', 'LG', '']

    for corp in tqdm(corp_list):
        code = get_code(stock_code, corp)
        date = datetime.strftime(datetime.now(), '%Y%m%d%H%M%S') # 
        df = pd.DataFrame() #   
        for num in range(1, 40): # 1~39 
            url = f'https://finance.naver.com/item/sise_time.nhn?code={code}&thistime={date}&page={num}'
            soup = get_soup(url)

            table_sec = soup.find('table')
            rows = table_sec.find_all('tr')

            temp = get_df(rows)
            if len(temp) != 0:
                temp[''] = date[:8]
                df = pd.concat([df, temp], ignore_index=True)

        #     csv 
        os.makedirs(f'./price_data/{corp}', exist_ok=True)
        file_name = datetime.strftime(datetime.now(), '%Y%m%d')
        df.to_csv(f'./price_data/{corp}/{file_name}.csv', encoding='utf8')

schedule.every().day.at("16:00").do(crawl_price_data) #  16 00 crawl_price_data  .
